      "content": "That sharp pain moving from your belly button to the lower right is a classic sign of appendicitis, not just gas or cramps, and you need to see a doctor immediately. You should not take strong ibuprofen or codeine because they can mask the symptoms and delay life-saving treatment. Instead, go to the emergency room right away to get an ultrasound or CT scan to confirm the diagnosis.",
      "source": "target",
